Creatives, this kitchen table rant post is for you.

Is it just me or has social media become a competition-over-community space? I notice a lot of ideas repeated without any reference to the source of inspiration. I notice it for other accounts as well as my own, down to the smallest details. Like so many others, this space is a creative outlet for me, and as I strive for uniqueness and to inspire, it hits at the core of my soul to see my own ideas echoed by bigger accounts, presenting them as their own.  I am tired of suppressing my own creativity in order to protect it. I’ll probably always remain small, but I refuse to stay quiet - on behalf of all who share their creative spirit here. There’s a good chance that if you authentically create and your vision is unique, you have felt this pain on some level. Imitation is NOT ALWAYS the sincerest, highest form of flattery.

To those who support others and always seem to give credit where credit is due: you are the community builders - I admire you, notice you, & thank you.

Creatives, here’s your reminder that although your work will always be vulnerable to imitation, your authenticity, inventiveness, & vision are untouchable.

End of rant. (Inspired by a series of observations over a long period of time - not by one single event or person.)

I took June & Della to @gammelgarden_of_scandia’s Swedish prayer service last Sunday (held in their 1850’s, unheated church) in celebration of Lucia Dagen. After the service, we went into the Välkommen Hus for coffee, Lucia buns, and a Christmas story. The girls loved our morning so much and hope to get into the 6:00 am candlelit service next year. We brought home a couple of the prettiest candoliers from their Butik to shine in our windows as a reminder of Lucia’s light. 🕯

It’s such a blessing that this community we live in really embraces and celebrates our rich, Scandinavian history. Thank you, @gammelgarden_of_scandia, for the most beautiful, Christmas experience ♥️

A few more garlands and strings of lights to hang, several trays of cookies to bake, all of the presents to wrap, gingerbread houses to decorate, a winter storm on the way, Christmas music playing, Christmas gin poured, sleeves rolled up, apron tied… we’re in the home stretch and “I don’t know what to say, except it’s Christmas and we’re all in misery.” - Ellen Griswold ♥️🥃🚬

📷: @johannagracerue
How do I still love them? ✨ It’s a daily miracle.

A belated Merry Christmas & Happy New Year from my family to you and yours ♥️ 

@johannagracerue
June & Blondie helped me shoot new tack for @natalie_millhouse & @thenorthcountrytack yesterday. It was so cold, but so pretty!

We surprised Della with this little guy and she’s still thinking it’s all just a dream. She has asked me a few times “mom, why am I crying?” Happy tears are confusing to a 5 year old 😂

He arrived here with very little human interaction, but has been so sweet, so gentle, and loves all of the new attention he has been getting: especially from the people closer to his own size.  His name is changing by the hour, so Della will let everyone know when she settles on one. 

Grandpa Ed did an exam on him and pointed out the coloring on his head and ears. He told us they call this a Medicine Hat. (It shows best in the last photo.) I had never heard of it, but this is what I read:

“Native American legends say that Medicine Hat horses were believed to have the magical ability to protect their riders from injury and death in battle. Additionally, they were said to warn their riders of danger. Other tribes would try to steal these horses in hopes of getting their good luck. For this reason, they were closely guarded.” - @cowgirlmagazine
Slow, northern winter days.. they seem so much longer in February. 🕯️ Trying to feel some sunshine in the little things.
@nickmundt turned 50 years old today, but rarely acts his age and has yet to show it. Happy Birthday, Nick! We love you!!!

If Lorena Wood were a pretty bathroom.. 

She was the inspiration behind creating this space. I see her in the ornate, antique mirrors, the clawfoot tub, the old lace, the etched glass, the curtains, the floral prints… every little detail. ✨ 

“I swear, Lorie Darlin’, you’re as pretty as the mornin’.”
- Gus McCrae 🤍🕯️

Della said, “His name is Piggy Fizz and that’s it. We’re done talking about it.”👩🏼‍⚖️

She named him after the old fashioned candy she likes from the Scandinavian gift shop.

A quick bathroom refresh we’ve put off for years! I didn’t have a vision for this neglected bathroom until a long stare over a cup of coffee revealed it few nights ago. I already had the wallpaper, I just didn’t know I would be using it in this room. Once I decided on moving forward with the wallpaper, the rest just fell right into place. 

The goal was to work with the tile we already had from our first remodel. Our latest addition wrapped around this room, so we lost the original window and it all felt too dark - I was NOT feeling any motivation to make this space pretty. 

It’s not 100% complete. I have a few to-dos left on my list; paint touch-ups, a little decorating, add a small shelf over the toilet, make a few changes to the vanity, plumbing fixtures, etc… but I’m already so happy with the transformation! 

@nickmundt: the baseboard, bead board, faux post/beam, crown moulding, and peg rail shelf 🔨👏🏼🏆

June & Della took the goats out for a walk through the woods a few weeks ago. The ice on the trees sounded like millions of little chimes as it broke off and dropped through branches. 

These girls and their little herd of friends… 🥹🤍

Small glimpses of Easter dinner at our house this year. 

Creating a nostalgia for my kids is what always inspires my holiday decorating. I remind myself that there will be a day to make things simple, pretty, and as colorless as I sometimes want them.. but for right now, as long as they’re young, I imagine the holidays (and their someday memories) through their eyes. They inspire the playfulness of the color, of the patterns, and of every kitschy little detail. I do not think every little detail will matter looking back: I just hope that if I paint enough of these details into the bigger picture of their childhood, at least a couple will stick around as memories and reminders of how much I love them. 🙏🏼
The old oak tree by the porch is feeling the kids’ love again. Winter was too long for all of us.

Our grain mill arrived yesterday and it is a BEAUTY! 🤍 I’ve been wanting to mill our own flour for the health benefits (especially for the kids) so I’ve been researching grain mills. I was leaning toward an electric mill, but June & Della really wanted a manual; as I read more about them, I changed my mind at the last minute from electric to manual.. and here we are. 🪄

Our wheat berries JUST arrived at the door. 🌾

So worth the wait!!!! 🥹

We lost our young pug, Toad, unexpectedly, almost 3 years ago. The kids have talked about him every single day since and Della prays for him every night at the dinner table. They have been waiting for another pug puppy, but wanted it to be as close to Toad as possible. Our prayers have been answered!!! 😭♥️

This little guy, from the same breeder, could be Toad’s clone. He acts like Toad, looks like Toad, sounds like Toad, smells like Toad, and IMMEDIATELY loved kids like Toad did. His level of excitement when he surprised the kids felt like he missed them as much as they’ve missed their little friend. 

The kids named him Elmer, but Della wants everyone to know that it is Elmer Spud. Welcome to the farm and our family, little porch potato. 💕
Just finished my annual kitten photos on the porch. This litter has been so sweet. They’re already old enough to go to new homes. That went by too fast. 🥹

Tillie & Elmer like to take breaks on the porch after running through leaks in the hose, stealing garden tools, and chasing chickens - their paces don’t align, but their hearts sure do. 🐆🦭

& let’s not even talk about that chippy porch floor. I get to repaint that this week. 😫

Life is in full bloom on the front porch again; daily sun tea, chickens in my planters, cats & dogs napping, good conversations & the best company.

Happy Father’s Day!! We feel very blessed to be celebrating a few of the best today. 

We love you, @nickmundt! Life has been quite the adventure with you as our guide.⛰️ Over these last few years with you, the kids have seen more horizon than I ever imagined I’d see in a lifetime. Thanks for all you do to provide this life for all of us!
Getting the kitchen cleaned up and ready for some red, white, and blue! 🇺🇸

I beaded these on the front porch. Color palette inspired by my surroundings. 🇺🇸 

Goodbye to another beautiful July.
These two today 👏🏼💓

Wildflower June & her horse, Blondie. 

Thanks for leading these two down the trail, @natalie_millhouse 🤍

Still loving summer, but starting to feel excited for another fall in this kitchen.🍂☕️ 

(Pictured: Fall 2022)

#farmhousekitchen

June won both of her classes at her horse show last weekend! 🤍👏🏼🥹 This cute team has been working hard and I am very proud of them. 

Thanks for guiding June & Blondie through it all, @natalie_millhouse!

☕️🕯️📻

My friend, @suzieschulte, taught June how to make her first quilt over the summer. (It’s VERY cute & I’ll share it soon.) Those lessons at Suzie’s became some of our favorite summer days & started something in both of us that we can’t seem to quit now. June is already working on her second quilt and I am currently working on two. (👆🏼This will be Della’s quilt for her bed.) 

Suzie sold us on a major sewing machine upgrade & sent us riding off into the sunset. So, if I’m not listening to an old country playlist and drinking coffee on the porch, this is where you’ll find me on these cold fall nights.
Homemade, freshly & manually milled wheat bread. It’s a lot of extra work, but so worth it: the flavor & texture is amazing.

I have a 15 year old today, so I took him for an early dirt road practice drive this morning. If all goes as planned, he’ll have his driving permit tomorrow. 😅 Jack reminded me that he has been operating tractors and all kinds of other equipment since he was about 6, so he feels prepared to drive my truck: I just had to see it to believe it.😅 We’ve done a lot of our growing up together, so this feels like a huge shift towards adulthood for both of us. 😂😬 Happy Birthday, Jackson James! Thank you for letting me post one photo and for approving a caption other than “mom.. stop.”

We lost our sweet Ethel last Wednesday. It was the morning after she mustered up just enough energy for me take these photos for June. I helped her stand to graze for about an hour that night, carried her to the barn when the sun went down, and she never made it to her feet again. We really miss her kind eyes, her crooked little jaw, and her excitement at the gate every morning for a little handful of sweet feed. We really loved this girl.

This may come as a surprise to most, but we are selling our house! We have poured so much of ourselves into this beautiful place, still love it more than I can put into words, and feel a little crazy for considering moving on from here, BUT, after giving this old farmhouse a new life, we feel ready to take on another project. If this is meant to be, it will happen; if not, we will stay and live happily ever after. 🤍 Only time will tell.

There is an endless supply of wild grapes on this property: filling this giant colander didn’t even make a dent on the fence line we picked from. 

@fuhrvickie spent the entire day in my kitchen, teaching us how to make her wild grape jelly. These are the best days. 🤍
& the result: almost 2 dozen jars of wild grape jelly. 🍇🤍 @fuhrvickie

“I am going to make everything around me beautiful - that will be my life.” 

Elsie De Wolfe

I catch random glimpses of my kids that leave me awestruck.. so amazed that they’re mine. Sometimes I get lucky in those moments and have a camera in my hands: this is an example of that perfect timing.

Loving a chicken the way Della loves “Cookie Muffin” is a risky business. 

Praying her little friend can stay strong through a Minnesota winter.
October 31st. We woke up to a change of scenery this morning.
null
Exploring grandma & grandpa’s maple ridge during the peak of fall color. 🍂 The light in their woods was a bright, warm gold, even on an overcast day. It never lasts long enough.

I’ve been holding onto fall this year, but slowing down, living in the present moment, and enjoying the natural timing of the seasons has been so good to my soul and home.

The weather is transitioning again, the trees have lost their color, and the Christmas storage is ringing.. 🔔

June, Della, and I made salt dough ornaments, inspired by the very creative & talented @missmustardseed 🤍 Both recipes we used were on her website where she also explains techniques & tricks. It was such a fun, relaxing project & now we’re hooked. We’ll be over here collecting cookie molds and dreaming up our next batch. ☕️

Della’s first year singing in the cutest Sankta Lucia program. The songs were in Swedish and these kids were so great: some only had a few weeks of practice ♥️

One of the things I love about where we live is how this community honors and celebrates our Scandinavian roots, especially at Christmastime: it’s magical.✨

Thanks for introducing us to this tradition, @laura_greene01 🤍
